@NODE rm_backup "Backup"
It's recommended that you make a working copy of your OctaMED disk and
store the original disk in a safe place. This will save you from a lot
of frustration if your OctaMED disk becomes corrupted. You are allowed
BY LAW to make two backup copies for your own personal use only!
@ENDNODE


